In [ ]:
res = {}
for instance_name, instance_grades in grades.items():
    res[instance_name] = {}
    for method_name, grade in instance_grades.items():
        meth_name = method_name.value.replace("_", " ").title()
        res[instance_name][meth_name] = [grade.avg, grade.min, grade.max, *grade.runtime]
In [ ]:
dfs = {}
for instance, methods in res.items():
    df = (
        pd.DataFrame.from_dict(
            methods,
            orient="index",
            columns=["Average Score", "Min Score", "Max Score", "Total runtime", "Per run runtime"],
        )
        .reset_index()
        .sort_values(by="Min Score")
        .reset_index(drop=True)
    )
    df.columns = [
        "Method",
        "Average Score",
        "Min Score",
        "Max Score",
        "Total runtime",
        "Per run runtime",
    ]
    df.index.name = instance
    dfs[instance] = df

Number of runs (average) for stopping condition 105s:

  • TSPC:
    • Large-scale neighborhood search no local search: 658
    • Large-scale neighborhood search with local search: 284
  • TSPD:
    • Large-scale neighborhood search no local search: 658
    • Large-scale neighborhood search with local search: 232

Large-scale neighborhood search without local search gives us very similar results. For the TSPC dataset LSN without LS we've obtained slightly better result (47k compared to 47.1k - really small difference).
On the other hand for the TSPD dataset LSN with LS we've obtained better result (43.3k compared to 44.5k).

As a destroy operator we've used deletion of 20-30% (chosen randomly) of the nodes (chosen randomly).
As a repair operator we've used greedy-regret weighted solution (with k=2 and equal weights 0.5 & 0.5).
